Convert try-fail-catch-ignore to assertThrows (#2472)

Convert try-fail-catch-ignore patterns to assertThrows in JUnit tests.

So, this:

```java
try {
  willThrowMyException();
  fail();
} catch (MyException e) {
  /* ignore */
}
```

becomes this:

```java
assertThrows(MyException.class, () -> willThrowMyException());
```

